    "   \"id\": \"c205bc25-45a5-4fee-903d-fddac4121efb\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"**Handling Missing Data**: Our initial scan revealed 1,134 missing values in bedrooms and similar gaps in bathrooms and sqft_living. By applying median imputation, we filled these gaps using a central tendency measure that is resistant to outliers. This ensures that extreme \\\"mansion\\\" prices in the King County dataset do not unfairly influence the replacement values for missing data, maintaining a more realistic distribution for the majority of homes.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Data Wrangling (Type Conversion)**: Converting the date column from a string to a datetime object is the most significant wrangling step. In its original format, the date was non-calculable text. As a datetime object, we can now extract specific time features (year, month, day) and calculate the Age of the House at Sale, which is a high-impact feature for price prediction.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"The post-cleaning verification confirms a 0% null rate across all 21,613 rows. The dataset is now structurally ready for the exploratory data analysis (EDA) phase.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
